I see - the test was expecting that `regular_field: 'normal text with {template} chars'` would have `{template}` sanitized to `[template]`. But when the whole object is passed to `formatObjectForTemplate()` and then `JSON.stringify()`, the entire thing becomes valid JSON, so the sanitizer doesn't touch it.

The sanitization only happens to email content (subject/body), not to the JSON-formatted candidate categories. Let me verify this understanding by checking what gets sanitized:

Looking back at the interpolation in ai-feature-extraction.ts:

```typescript
const context = {
  email: {
    from: formatEmailAddress(email.from),  // ← sanitized
    subject: email.subject || '',           // ← sanitized
    body: getEmailBodyText(email),          // ← sanitized
  },
  candidateCategories: formatObjectForTemplate(candidateCategories), // ← NOT sanitized (stays as JSON)
  detectedAttributes: formatObjectForTemplate(detectedAttributes),   // ← NOT sanitized (stays as JSON)
};
```

So the test expectation is WRONG. The `{template}` in `regular_field` is part of the candidate categories JSON and should NOT be sanitized. The test should verify that it's preserved:

